{"$schema":"https://ps-wiki.github.io/schema/v1/term.schema.json","id":"transient-stability","title":"Transient Stability","description":"The ability to maintain synchronism.","language":"en","tags":["stability","system-operator","pjm"],"related":["stability","transient-stability-assessment","dynamic-stability"],"version":"1.0.0","breaking":false,"dates":{"created":"2025-12-02","last_modified":"2025-12-02"},"authors":[{"name":"Jinning Wang","url":"https://jinningwang.github.io"}],"content":{"sections":[{"order":1,"id":"definition-by-pjm","title":"Definition by PJM","type":"definition","source_keys":["pjm2025m3v69"],"page":"p64, Revision 69","body_md":"> The ability of a generating unit or a group of generating units to maintain synchronism folowing a relatively severe and sudden system disturbance. The first few cycles are the most critical time period.\n"}]}}